Package com.ftp.client

Class FTPClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ftp.client.FTPClient

  • public class FTPClient
extends java.lang.Object
    This is basic class that represents client connecting to remote FTPServer. It uses Socket for establishing connection to remote server with given username, password, host, port and communicate with FTPTransferObject. It has 2 main threads, one for reading and one for writing to socket input/output stream. Upon connecting, client sends username and password as plain String and after that runs read thread which is responsible for listening and reading FTPTransferObject from socket. On connecting server sends object that contains TreeItem with folders/files from server. Thread for writing to socket output stream runs on command while reading thread works infinitely (until connection closes).

    • Method Detail

      • createSocket

        public boolean createSocket​()
        This method is used for creating socket and connecting to server. On connecting it sends login credentials and starts reading thread that is responsible for listening to socket and accepting FTPTransferObject.

      • readFromSocket

        public void readFromSocket​()
        This method creates thread for reading from socket stream. It is called after successful connection to server. Method reads FTPTransferObject from input stream, and after that reads file bytes (if there is any. Tree view (server's file explorer) is updated on every change on server side.

      • writeToSocket

        public void writeToSocket​(java.io.File pathClient,
                          java.io.File pathServer,
                          FTPCommand command)
        This method creates thread that is used for sending FTPTransferObject to server. After object, if required, encrypted file bytes are sent. It runs on command (unlike read thread which runs infinitely until connection is closed).
        Parameters:
        pathClient - Path from client (if file needs to be sent)
        pathServer - Path on server side (if file needs to be received or folder needs to be created)
        command - Command to be executed

      • writeObjectToStream

        public void writeObjectToStream​(java.io.File pathClient,
                                java.io.File pathServer,
                                FTPCommand command)
                         throws java.io.IOException
        This method is used for sending object from server to client. Before sending, object length is sent first, represented as string maximum length of 16 bytes. Object represent FTPTransferObject with command, credentials for authentication, paths, file size...
        Parameters:
        pathClient - Client's file path
        pathServer - Server's file/folder path
        command - Command to be executed
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is problem with object, if there is socket or stream problem

      • writeFileToStream

        public void writeFileToStream​(java.io.File pathClient,
                              boolean empty)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        This method send file as encrypted bytes to server (if required). File size was already sent in object. Method uses BufferedInputStream for reading file by chunks, each chunk is 512 bytes length, and writes them directly to stream.
        Parameters:
        pathClient - Path from client's file that needs to be sent
        empty - If there is no need for file to be sent, this flag is set to true and synchronization byte is sent
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is problem with file, or stream

      • readObjectFromStream

        public FTPTransferObject readObjectFromStream​()
                                       throws java.io.IOException,
                                              java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        This method reads object from stream. First it reads object size that is sent from server, and then FTPTransferObject.
        Returns:
        Read object from stream
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If object is not read correctly, or there is some stream problem (bytes not read correctly)
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - If there is problem with class

      • readFileFromStream

        public void readFileFromStream​(FTPTransferObject readObject)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        This method reads file from stream and stores it in client's directory. From given FTPTransferObject file size is read, and then, with 512 bytes buffer, file is read and stored.
        Parameters:
        readObject - Read object from stream before reading file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is problem with file or stream
